00:56:43.909 --> 00:57:02.170
Our postcard this month

00:57:02.170 --> 00:57:04.170
to the beautiful country

00:57:04.170 --> 00:57:06.170
of Paraguay

00:57:06.170 --> 00:57:08.170
Paraguay is a landlocked country

00:57:08.170 --> 00:57:10.170
in the heart of South America

00:57:10.170 --> 00:57:12.170
with a population of about 7

00:57:12.170 --> 00:57:14.170
million

00:57:14.170 --> 00:57:16.170
the Paraguay river runs from north

00:57:16.170 --> 00:57:18.170
to south dividing the country

00:57:18.170 --> 00:57:20.170
the east is characterized

00:57:20.170 --> 00:57:22.170
by rolling hills

00:57:22.170 --> 00:57:24.170
fertile fields

00:57:24.170 --> 00:57:26.170
some of which have red

00:57:26.170 --> 00:57:28.170
soil and thick forests

00:57:28.170 --> 00:57:30.170
in contrast

00:57:30.170 --> 00:57:32.170
to the region

00:57:32.170 --> 00:57:34.170
has a sparse population

00:57:34.170 --> 00:57:36.170
coarse grass

00:57:36.170 --> 00:57:38.170
scrub forest

00:57:38.170 --> 00:57:40.170
vast swamps

00:57:40.170 --> 00:57:42.170
and diverse colorful

00:57:42.170 --> 00:57:44.170
tropical birds

00:57:44.170 --> 00:57:46.170
Paraguay has two

00:57:46.170 --> 00:57:48.170
official languages

00:57:48.170 --> 00:57:50.170
Spanish and Guani

00:57:50.170 --> 00:57:52.170
and when the two languages

00:57:52.170 --> 00:57:54.170
mix you get

00:57:54.170 --> 00:57:56.170
Jopara

00:57:56.170 --> 00:57:58.170
which is frequently used today

00:57:58.170 --> 00:58:00.170
Paraguay's theocratic history

00:58:00.170 --> 00:58:02.170
has been dragged

00:58:02.170 --> 00:58:04.170
randomly sent to his home

00:58:04.170 --> 00:58:06.170
from world headquarters

00:58:06.170 --> 00:58:08.170
This moved him to order studies

00:58:08.170 --> 00:58:10.170
in the scriptures

00:58:10.170 --> 00:58:12.170
In 1906

00:58:12.170 --> 00:58:14.170
he and his brother-in-law

00:58:14.170 --> 00:58:16.170
baptized each other

00:58:16.170 --> 00:58:18.170
becoming the first

00:58:18.170 --> 00:58:20.170
in Paraguay to accept Bible truth

00:58:20.170 --> 00:58:22.170
In 1924

00:58:22.170 --> 00:58:24.170
Juan Munois

00:58:24.170 --> 00:58:26.170
a faithful missionary

00:58:26.170 --> 00:58:28.170
from Spain

00:58:28.170 --> 00:58:29.170
arrived to spread the kingdom message

00:58:29.170 --> 00:58:32.170
including Paraguay.

00:58:32.170 --> 00:58:36.170
Then in 1934, brothers Martonfi,

00:58:36.170 --> 00:58:40.170
Coros, and Reibach entered the country

00:58:40.170 --> 00:58:43.170
despite the ongoing Chaco War.

00:58:43.170 --> 00:58:47.170
Their efforts paid off when the first congregation

00:58:47.170 --> 00:58:50.170
was formed five years later.

00:58:50.170 --> 00:58:54.170
Decades of political instability resulted in a decree

00:58:54.170 --> 00:58:58.170
revoking the organization's legal status

00:58:58.170 --> 00:59:01.170
in 1979.

00:59:01.170 --> 00:59:04.170
As a result, the brothers had to conduct meetings

00:59:04.170 --> 00:59:10.170
in small groups at private homes or in isolated areas.

00:59:10.170 --> 00:59:14.170
Fortunately, 12 years later in 1991,

00:59:14.170 --> 00:59:17.170
the organization was legally recognized

00:59:17.170 --> 00:59:20.170
after the fall of the military regime.

00:59:20.170 --> 00:59:24.170
Did the publishers dwindle during those years?

00:59:24.170 --> 00:59:28.170
Sadly, the number of publishers doubled in size.

00:59:28.170 --> 00:59:32.170
Today, there are over 11,000 publishers

00:59:32.170 --> 00:59:35.170
who conduct about 10,000 Bible studies

00:59:35.170 --> 00:59:40.170
and attend 183 congregations.

00:59:40.170 --> 00:59:42.170
In the western part of the country,

00:59:42.170 --> 00:59:48.170
we find the Philadelphia Espanol and Loma Plata Guarani congregations.

00:59:48.170 --> 00:59:52.170
The 95 publishers of these two congregations

00:59:52.170 --> 00:59:56.170
conduct an average of 155 Bible studies

00:59:56.170 --> 01:00:00.170
and preach in Spanish, Guarani,

01:00:00.170 --> 01:00:03.170
Low German, and Niva Clay.

